                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13860674" author="guozhang" created="Thu, 2 Jan 2014 19:55:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;1) List option will always get all the topics, only describe option will take the topic specification.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) the getTopics function does not check if opts.topicOpt is specified, and hence throws the NullPointerException.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Proposed solution: check topicOpt unless it is the list option.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13860804" author="guozhang" created="Thu, 2 Jan 2014 21:38:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I tried the following with the current trunk HEAD and did not hit the Exception:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. start ZK&lt;br/&gt;
2. start one broker&lt;br/&gt;
3. bin/kafka-topics.sh --zookeeper localhost:2181 --describe returns empty.&lt;br/&gt;
4. create a topic&lt;br/&gt;
5. bin/kafka-topics.sh --zookeeper localhost:2181 --list returns the topic&lt;br/&gt;
6. bin/kafka-topics.sh --zookeeper localhost:2181 --describe returns the description of the topic.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13860897" author="guozhang" created="Thu, 2 Jan 2014 22:49:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can re-produce this issue now, was having an older jar before.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13860919" author="guozhang" created="Thu, 2 Jan 2014 23:10:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created reviewboard &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/16579/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/16579/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
